15/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Parliament approved on Monday (March 14th) the government reshuffle proposed by Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic. 
A total of 129 out of 250 lawmakers supported the new cabinet. 
Most members of the opposition parties were not present for the vote. 
The changes will reduce the number of ministries from 24 to 17. 
The cabinet itself will consist of 21 ministers, six less than now. 
Cvetkovic will also assume the role of finance minister. 
(Tanjug, Beta, RTS, B92 - 14/03/11)
